CROSSING THE GREAT SMOKIES from Gatlinburg, Tennessee Twelve miles of steady climbing on gravel road cut from the sides of the mountains. No fences, with sheer drops of hundreds of feet over the side. At many places it was impossible for cars to pass. We encountered no more than a half dozen cars on the whole trip to Bryson City, N. C.
